that "it may prove to be the case that we got whipsawed -- that we pulled the recession forecast at just the wrong time.That's the forecasting business
However risky the business, it's brisk these days.Wall Street economists are forecasting about everything from broad economic trends to the dinkiest monthly indicator
This isn't the quiet economic science practiced in the universities.This is the commercial version
Mr. Straszheim meets confrontation that often occurs in inverse proportion to the size of the client.No sophisticated professional expects economists to be right all the time
