Reports of Dr. Toseland's findings in the British press have triggered widespread concern among diabetics there.Both the British Diabetic Association and the Committee on Safety in Medicines -- Britain's equivalent of the U.S. FDA -- recently issued statements noting the lack of hard scientific evidence to support Dr. Toseland's findings
