On so-called Manic Monday, Oct. 16, stock prices plunged across Europe and trading problems erupted.London had some problems, too
London had some problems, too.The London exchange's electronic price-reporting system provided only indicative, or non-firm, prices for about 40 minutes on Manic Monday
