The S&P 500 index futures "transferred the identity of 500 stocks into one unit-making them a simple commodity to trade.It took away the need to know the bad third-quarter report of IBM, for example
Of course, portfolio trading -- the increasingly common practice of buying or selling baskets of actual stocks -- also treats stocks as homogenous commodities. "There is a class of investor that wants to be exposed" to the whole market, says Sandip Bhagat, assistant vice president at Travelers Investment Management Co
There is a class of investor that wants to be exposed" to the whole market, says Sandip Bhagat, assistant vice president at Travelers Investment Management Co.The S&P futures are merely a "cheaper and quicker" way to get access to all 500 stocks, he says
