The stock market correction of Oct. 13, 1989, was a grim reminder of the Oct. 19, 1987 market collapse.Since, like earthquakes, stock market disturbances will always be with us, it is prudent to take all possible precautions against another such market collapse
But there are times when they seize up, and panicky sellers cannot find buyers.That's just what happened in the October 1987 crash
That's just what happened in the October 1987 crash.As the market tumbled, disorderly market conditions prevailed: The margins between buying bids and selling bids widened; trading in many stocks was suspended; orders took unduly long to be executed; and many specialists stopped trading altogether
