the agency is studying the Friday the 13th market plunge, including how current circuit breakers affected the market that day and the following Monday.After the study, the SEC would be willing to consider adding new circuit breakers or fine-tuning the current ones
Circuit breakers, designed to give the markets a breather in cases of sharp price movements, curb trading of futures or stocks at various trigger points.At certain points during the Friday the 13th drop, circuit breakers kicked in on the futures market, slowing trading at times
At certain points during the Friday the 13th drop, circuit breakers kicked in on the futures market, slowing trading at times.A circuit breaker that would have closed down the New York Stock Exchange wasn't tripped
