Christopher Cox's Oct. 13 editorial-page article "Toward More Crippling Lawsuits . . ." misses the point.The 1989 Americans With Disabilities Act is about eliminating discriminatory barriers
it is clear that our constitutionally mandated civil rights have evolved not through the goodness of people's hearts but through legislation and constitutional amendments.This is how American women won the right to vote
For the more than 43 million Americans with disabilities, the 1989 Americans With Disabilities Act provides the missing piece.Disabled Americans have had their civil rights guaranteed in all federally funded programs since Section 504 was passed as a part of the 1973 Rehabilitation Act.The 1989 act simply extends these guarantees to the private sector
