Now, after only a dozen moves, spectators were looking for a mating combination.On a demonstration board, emcee Shelby Lyman showed a quick kill initiated by a knight sacrifice
Mr. Kasparov's continuation was slower but, in the end, just as deadly.He won D.T.'s queen for two minor pieces and two pawns -- not enough compensation, in this position, to give the computer much hope
