Though the service is available only in California, Telelawyer founder Michael Cane says he plans to franchise it in other states.He says his aim is to reach people who are bedridden, have no access to transportation, can't find a lawyer to take their case or simply can't afford lawyers' consultation fees
that he isn't using the telephone to lure clients to his doorstep. "We will only deal with clients on the phone
We will only deal with clients on the phone.We have no in-office business
