Two decades ago, the Small Business Administration reported Yale Prof.Albert Reiss's landmark study of crime against 2,500 small businesses drawn from national IRS records.He found that monetary crime losses, as a proportion of gross receipts, were 37 times higher for small businesses than for large ones
