The experiments involve encircling a thin rod of palladium metal with a wire of platinum and plunging the two electrodes into "heavy" water in which the hydrogen atoms are a doubly heavy form known as deuterium.When an electric current is applied to the palladium and platinum electrodes, the heavy water did begin to break up, or dissociate
When an electric current is applied to the palladium and platinum electrodes, the heavy water did begin to break up, or dissociate.Ordinarily the electrolysis, or breakup, of the water would consume almost all of the electrical energy
