Some may have forgotten what it's like to invest during a recession.Different tactics are called for, as losing money becomes easier and making money becomes tougher
In a nutshell, pros advise investors who expect a slowdown to hold fewer stocks than usual and to favor shares of big companies in "defensive" industries.A heavy dose of cash is prescribed, along with a heavier-than-usual allotment to bonds -- preferably government bonds
because recessions often take investors by surprise. "They always seem to come a bit later than you expect
