It's an "absolute necessity" to get out of junk bonds when a recession is in the offing.Such bonds are very sensitive to the downside
Municipal bonds are generally a bit safer than corporate bonds in a recession, but not as safe as bonds issued by the federal government.During an economic slump, local tax revenues often go down, raising the risks associated with at least some municipals
