The Packwood plan, as expected, would allow individuals to exclude from income 5% of the gain from the sale of a capital asset held for more than one year.The exclusion would rise five percentage points for each year the asset was held, until it reached a maximum of 35% after seven years.The exclusion would apply to assets sold after Oct. 1
