Corporations need liquidity, in the form of borrowed funds.Without liquidity from the junk-bond market or cash flow from profits, they look to the government
which obediently assists the natural motions of the capitalist economy with charity in the form of cuts in the capital-gains tax rate or bailouts.The consequence can be inflation, brought on as the effect of a desperate bid to avoid the deflationary shock of a sudden crash
